---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Malenia, Blade of Miquella - Ultimate Boss Guide";
const description = "Complete Malenia boss guide with moveset breakdown, dodge strategies, cheese tactics, and optimal builds for Elden Ring's hardest boss.";
---

<Layout {title} {description}>
  <article class="boss-guide">
    <h1>⚔️ Malenia, Blade of Miquella - Ultimate Boss Guide</h1>

    <div class="boss-overview">
      <div class="boss-info">
        <h2>Boss Overview</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Location:</strong> Haligtree Roots (Consecrated Snowfield → Miquella's Haligtree → Elphael, Brace of the Haligtree)</li>
          <li><strong>Recommended Level:</strong> 120-150</li>
          <li><strong>Phase Count:</strong> 2 phases (transforms at 50% HP)</li>
          <li><strong>Difficulty:</strong> ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (Hardest boss in base game)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="warning-box">
        <h3>⚠️ Why Malenia is Brutal</h3>
        <p>Malenia heals on every hit she lands — even blocked hits. This means defensive play alone won't win. You need aggressive dodging and burst damage windows.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="moveset">
      <h2>🗡️ Phase 1 Moveset Breakdown</h2>
      <p>Phase 1 is learnable. Here are her 5 most dangerous attacks:</p>

      <div class="move-card">
        <h3>1. Waterfowl Dance (The Killer Move)</h3>
        <p class="move-description">Her signature attack. She leaps, pauses, then unleashes a 3-part flurry:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>First flurry:</strong> 3 rapid slashes</li>
          <li><strong>Second flurry:</strong> 5 rapid slashes</li>
          <li><strong>Final flurry:</strong> 7 rapid slashes</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="dodge-tip">
          <strong>✅ How to Dodge:</strong> Back away during the pause. When she starts the first flurry, run directly <strong>away</strong> from her. For the second and third flurries, you must <strong>dodge-roll into her</strong> (toward her hitbox) to slip between the blade swings.
        </div>
        <div class="dodge-tip alternative">
          <strong>💡 Alternative:</strong> Use Bloodhound's Step ash of war to roll through the attack invincibly.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="move-card">
        <h3>2. Quick Slash Combo</h3>
        <p class="move-description">A fast 2-3 hit combo. She telegraphs with a slight wind-up, then strikes horizontally.</p>
        <div class="dodge-tip">
          <strong>✅ How to Dodge:</strong> Roll <strong>toward her right side</strong> (her sword arm). Stay close and punish after the last hit.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="move-card">
        <h3>3. Thrusting Sweep</h3>
        <p class="move-description">She pulls her blade back for a long thrust, then sweeps in an arc.</p>
        <div class="dodge-tip">
          <strong>✅ How to Dodge:</strong> Roll <strong>perpendicular to her thrust direction</strong> (to the side, not back). Roll through the sword during the sweep.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="move-card">
        <h3>4. Aerial Dive</h3>
        <p class="move-description">She leaps high and plunges downward with a spinning slash.</p>
        <div class="dodge-tip">
          <strong>✅ How to Dodge:</strong> Sprint away from the shadow on the ground. Roll when the shadow stops moving.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="move-card">
        <h3>5. Spinning Slash</h3>
        <p class="move-description">A 360-degree horizontal spin attack. Looks unavoidable but has a tell.</p>
        <div class="dodge-tip">
          <strong>✅ How to Dodge:</strong> Roll <strong>directly into her</strong> as she starts spinning. You'll pass through the blade's sweet spot and take no damage.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="phase2">
      <h2>🦋 Phase 2: Goddess of Rot</h2>
      <p>At 50% HP, Malenia transforms. New moves are added to her moveset:</p>

      <div class="move-card">
        <h3>New Attack: Scarlet Rot Bloom</h3>
        <p class="move-description">She slams her prosthetic hand into the ground, creating a rotating rot pool.</p>
        <div class="dodge-tip">
          <strong>✅ How to Dodge:</strong> Keep moving. The pool rotates clockwise, so strafe <strong>counter-clockwise</strong> to stay ahead of it.
        </div>
        <div class="warning-box">
          <strong>⚠️ Rot Buildup:</strong> If you get hit by the rot pool, you'll start accumulating Scarlet Rot. Bring <strong>Preserving Boluses</strong> to cure it, or equip <strong>Mushroom Crown</strong> (+20% immunity).
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="move-card">
        <h3>New Attack: Phantom Slash Wave</h3>
        <p class="move-description">She swings her blade, sending a projectile wave of rot energy across the arena.</p>
        <div class="dodge-tip">
          <strong>✅ How to Dodge:</strong> Roll <strong>perpendicular to the wave</strong> (sideways). The wave is narrow and easy to dodge if you don't panic-roll backward.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dodge-tip">
        <strong>💡 Phase 2 Strategy:</strong> Her Waterfowl Dance now has rot on the final flurry. Use the same dodge pattern, but be extra careful on the last set of slashes — one hit means rot buildup.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cheese-strats">
      <h2>🧀 Cheese Strategies (If You Just Want to Win)</h2>

      <div class="cheese-card">
        <h3>Strategy 1: Mimic Tear + Bleed Build</h3>
        <p><strong>Why it works:</strong> The Mimic Tear spirit ash draws aggro, letting you attack safely. Bleed builds proc Blood Loss quickly, which doesn't heal her.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Spirit Ash:</strong> Mimic Tear (level 10)</li>
          <li><strong>Weapon:</strong> Rivers of Blood (Katana) or Eleonora's Poleblade</li>
          <li><strong>Ash of War:</strong> Bloodflame Blade or Corpse Wax Cutter</li>
          <li><strong>Talisman:</strong> Lord of Blood's Exultation (+20% attack power when blood loss procs nearby)</li>
          <li><strong>Strategy:</strong> Summon Mimic, let it tank. Flank and spam weapon skills to proc bleed. Repeat.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="cheese-card">
        <h3>Strategy 2: Magic Spam (Sorcery Build)</h3>
        <p><strong>Why it works:</strong> You can stay at range and avoid most melee attacks entirely.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Staff:</strong> Lusat's Glintstone Staff or Carian Regal Scepter</li>
          <li><strong>Spells:</strong> Comet Azur (burst), Ranni's Dark Moon (slow + damage), Adula's Moonblade (mobile)</li>
          <li><strong>Talisman:</strong> Radagon Icon (faster casting), Graven-Mass Talisman (+8% sorcery damage)</li>
          <li><strong>Strategy:</strong> Stay at max range. When she approaches, cast Ranni's Dark Moon to slow her, then back off and resume Comet spam.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="warning-box">
          <strong>⚠️ Warning:</strong> You still need to dodge Waterfowl Dance. When she starts the leap, immediately sprint away and prepare to dodge-roll into her flurry.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cheese-card">
        <h3>Strategy 3: Bleed + Freeze (Optimal Melee)</h3>
        <p><strong>Why it works:</strong> Bleed procs stagger her, and freeze reduces her damage output. This is the most reliable melee strategy.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Weapon:</strong> Rivers of Blood (Katana)</li>
          <li><strong>Ash of War:</strong> Bloodflame Blade</li>
          <li><strong>Off-hand:</strong> Ice affinity on second weapon (or use Frost Grease)</li>
          <li><strong>Talisman:</strong> Lord of Blood's Exultation, Rotten Winged Sword Insignia (+attack on consecutive hits)</li>
          <li><strong>Strategy:</strong> Apply frost first, then spam Corpse Piler (weapon skill) to proc bleed. Repeat the cycle.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="builds">
      <h2>🛡️ Optimal Builds for Malenia</h2>

      <div class="build-card">
        <h3>Melee Build: Bleed Samurai</h3>
        <table>
          <tr>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Equipment</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Weapon</td>
            <td><strong>Rivers of Blood</strong> (Katana)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Ash of War</td>
            <td><strong>Corpse Piler</strong> (built-in) or <strong>Bloodflame Blade</strong></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Talisman 1</td>
            <td><strong>Lord of Blood's Exultation</strong> (+20% ATK on blood loss)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Talisman 2</td>
            <td><strong>Rotten Winged Sword Insignia</strong> (ramp damage)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Talisman 3</td>
            <td><strong>Millicent's Prosthesis</strong> (+dexterity, +attack on chain)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Talisman 4</td>
            <td><strong>Green Turtle Talisman</strong> (stamina recovery)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Stats Priority</td>
            <td>Arcane 50 → Vigor 40 → Dexterity 30 → Endurance 25</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="build-card">
        <h3>Magic Build: Comet Sorcerer</h3>
        <table>
          <tr>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Equipment</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Staff</td>
            <td><strong>Lusat's Glintstone Staff</strong> (found in Sellia Hideaway)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Spells</td>
            <td><strong>Comet Azur</strong>, <strong>Ranni's Dark Moon</strong>, <strong>Terra Magicus</strong> (buff)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Talisman 1</td>
            <td><strong>Radagon Icon</strong> (faster casting)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Talisman 2</td>
            <td><strong>Graven-Mass Talisman</strong> (+8% sorcery damage)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Talisman 3</td>
            <td><strong>Moon of Nokstella</strong> (+memory slots)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Talisman 4</td>
            <td><strong>Green Turtle Talisman</strong> (stamina for dodging)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Stats Priority</td>
            <td>Intelligence 60 → Mind 30 → Vigor 40 → Endurance 20</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="phase-transitions">
      <h2>⏱️ Phase Transition Strategy</h2>
      <p>The transition from Phase 1 to Phase 2 is dangerous. She becomes invulnerable during the transformation cutscene, then immediately attacks.</p>

      <div class="tip-box">
        <h3>✅ What to Do:</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>When her HP hits 50%, <strong>immediately sprint away</strong> to maximum distance.</li>
          <li>During the cutscene, prepare your strongest buff (e.g., <strong>Terra Magicus</strong>, <strong>Flame Grant</strong>, or <strong>Flask of Wondrous Physick</strong>).</li>
          <li>As soon as you regain control, <strong>keep running</strong>. She'll do a ground slam that creates a rot shockwave.</li>
          <li>Wait for her recovery animation, then go in with your burst damage.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="warning-box">
        <strong>⚠️ Critical:</strong> Do NOT stand still during the transition. Many players die here because they're watching the animation. Keep moving.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="final-tips">
      <h2>🎯 Final Tips</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Use Mimic Tear.</strong> It's not cheating — it's a tool. The distraction alone is worth it.</li>
        <li><strong>Don't get greedy.</strong> Land 2-3 hits, then reposition. Her counter-attacks are lethal.</li>
        <li><strong>Learn Waterfowl Dance.</strong> It's the hardest move, but once you can consistently dodge it, the fight becomes manageable.</li>
        <li><strong>Bring Preserving Boluses.</strong> Craft 10-15 before the fight. Rot will kill you if you're not prepared.</li>
        <li><strong>Patience wins.</strong> Malenia punishes aggression. Wait for openings, don't force them.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="summary">
      <h2>📋 Quick Reference Summary</h2>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Situation</th>
          <th>Best Response</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Waterfowl Dance</td>
          <td><strong>Run away → Roll into her</strong> for each flurry</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Quick Combo</td>
          <td><strong>Roll to her right side</strong> and counter</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Thrust Attack</td>
          <td><strong>Roll perpendicular</strong> (sideways)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Aerial Dive</td>
          <td><strong>Sprint from shadow</strong>, roll when it stops</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Rot Pool (Phase 2)</td>
          <td><strong>Strafe counter-clockwise</strong> to stay ahead</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Phase Transition</td>
          <td><strong>Sprint away</strong>, buff up, wait for opening</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </section>

    <div class="call-to-action">
      <h2>🏆 You Got This!</h2>
      <p>Malenia is the ultimate test of patience and skill in Elden Ring. Even if you cheese her, take the time to learn her moveset — it's worth it for the satisfaction of a clean fight. Good luck, Tarnished!</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .boss-guide {
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .boss-overview {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .boss-info, .warning-box {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .warning-box {
    background: #fff3cd;
    border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
  }

  .boss-info ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .boss-info li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
  }

  .move-card {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #c41e3a;
  }

  .move-description {
    color: #555;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .dodge-tip {
    background: #d4edda;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #28a745;
  }

  .dodge-tip.alternative {
    background: #d1ecf1;
    border-left-color: #17a2b8;
  }

  .cheese-card, .build-card {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
  }

  .build-card table {
    width: 100%;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .tip-box {
    background: #d4edda;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid #28a745;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .tip-box h3 {
    border: none;
  }

  .summary table {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .call-to-action {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .call-to-action h2 {
    color: #ffd700;
    border: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .boss-overview {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
